@flexiarg relationship-coherence/narrative-suspension
@title Hold It Open: Incoherence Over a Distorting Order
@sigils [∅/懸]
@keywords no-narratives, narrative-ethics, non-labeling, hold-open, disponibilite, whatever-you-decide, life-writing-ethics
@audience correspondents resisting premature closure
@references [relationship-coherence/rupture-repair relationship-coherence/low-pressure-bid]
@references-extra ["Instance of origin: 2026-04-08 — Joe: 'With *no narratives* and a total jettisoning of certain previously formed assumptions about you, I feel quite open hearted.' Recurs as a stance he names 'my narrative ethics' (2026-05-18) and as the standing reply to labels ('Julia's got a boyfriend but she's in denial' -> 'Whatever you decide!', 2026-05-11). Resonant with Julia's own scholarship (life-writing ethics; the essay as anti-totalising form) and with Gide via 2026-03-27, 'incoherence is better than a distorting order'."]
@tone declarative
@style pattern

! conclusion: When a label or story threatens to foreclose what the relationship is, decline to over-determine it; hold it open on purpose. Here coherence is maintained by *refusing* a distorting order, not by imposing one.

  + context: This is the reflexive pattern of the set: a coherence move that works by withholding closure. Both parties are professionally and temperamentally suspicious of totalising narratives (life-writing ethics; assemblage/rhizome; Spinozan 'living in line with reality'), and they extend that ethic to their own bond.

  + IF:
    a ready-made category ('boyfriend', 'this is X') or a premature story about where it's all going presents itself as the thing to settle now.

  + HOWEVER:
    a shared world genuinely needs *some* mutual understanding to cohere; pure open-endedness can shade into avoidance, leaving one party carrying an unspoken story alone. The discipline is to hold open without going dark.

  + THEN:
    decline the label lightly ('whatever you decide'), share the *sentiment* without forcing a formed thought ('I don't even have any formed thoughts but I do have some warm sentiments I wanted to share'), and let structure be discovered rather than stipulated.

  + BECAUSE:
    a distorting order imposed early would mis-describe a thing still becoming; suspending the narrative keeps the description faithful to the territory as it moves. The coherence being protected is the freedom of the shared world to remain itself.

  + NEXT-STEPS:
    - Balance against silence: pair with relationship-coherence/rupture-repair so 'holding open' never becomes 'going dark' — sentiments still get voiced.
    - Failure twin, premature-labeling: settling the category to relieve one's own anxiety, at the cost of mis-naming what is actually there.
